# Cursor Rules for NexSupply

## Architecture Standards

- pages/: UI layout only. No complex logic. Max 200 lines/file.

- services/: All API calls (Gemini, Database).

- components/: Reusable UI elements.

- state/: Session state management.

- utils/: Configuration and helpers.

## Coding Standards

- Secrets: Use utils.config.Config. Never hardcode keys.

- Gemini: Use timeout=60.

- UI: Use st.columns for layout, st.markdown for custom CSS.

## Cursor Behavior

- Always reference @file when editing.

- Create __init__.py automatically in new folders.

